(1, 'ALX Project', 'By Aklilu Mandefro', '95401600_1524766758.jpg', 'blog,tech blog,tricks,hacks,technology news,fantastic blog', 'My name is Aklilu Mandefro from Gondar, Ethiopia, having 7+ experiences in PHP, Git, WordPress, MySQL, SQL, JavaScript, Java, HTML and CSS. I have worked on around 18+ projects. I love programming, coding and most of my time goes in learning the best ways to write clean code. When I am not found coding, I can be seen helping out tech geeks. I am always open to help others. ', '', '', '', 'Gondar Fasil Castle, Ethiopia', 'My name is Aklilu Mandefro from Gondar, Ethiopia with 7+ years of experience as a Software Engineer, Researcher and IT Instructor. While working as a Software Engineer I have worked on 18+ software design and development Projects that can solve the glitches in the Community. One of such Project is an ERP system that I designed and developed with my team for Water Supply and Sewerage Services provider Organizations for more than 3 Cities in Ethiopia. This is really a system that changed such organizations’ manual, tedious and inconvenient way of running businesses into modernized, easy to use, convenient and more productive. <br><br>\r\nAs a Researcher from Mega and Virtual Computer Research Centers, I conducted more than 4 research works, 3 of which are published online. I am a member of 6 International Research Journals like Indian Journal of Science and Technology, Asian Journal of research in Computer Science as a Research/Article Reviewer and received 6 certificates of excellence in reviewing from all of these Journals. \r\n          <p><strong>  RESEARCH PUBLICATIONS </strong><br>\r\n      \r\n1. Aklilu Mandefro Messele and Melkamu Addisu.. “Model to Determine Factors Affecting Students Academic Performance: The Case of Amhara Region Agency of Competency, Ethiopia”, \r\nInternational Research Journal of Science and Technology, 1(2), 75-87, 2020 <br>\r\nAvailable at:<a href=\" https://irjst.com/wp-content/uploads/March2020-v1-i2/IRJST122002.pdf\"><font color=\"blue\">https://irjst.com/wp-content/uploads/March2020-v1-i2/IRJST122002.pdf</font></a> \r\n<br><br>\r\n2. Aklilu Mandefro Messele. “A Bio-Inspired Reward-Based Message Forwarding for Vehicular Social Network”, International Research Journal of Science and Technology, 1 (2) 106-119, 2020.\r\n<br>\r\nAvailable at:<a href=\"https://irjst.com/wp-content/uploads/March2020-v1-i2/IRJST122006.pdf\"> <font color=\"blue\">https://irjst.com/wp-content/uploads/March2020-v1-i2/IRJST122006.pdf</font></a>\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n3. Aklilu Mandefro Messele, “Comparing K-Means and Expectation Maximization Algorithm to Cluster Amharic Noun Terms”, Journal of Multidimensional Research and Review (JMRR), Vol.1, Iss.1, pp. 31-56, 2020\r\n<br>\r\nAvailable at: <a href=\" http://jmrr.org/V1I1/V1I1P_20_04_03.pdf\"><font color=\"blue\"> http://jmrr.org/V1I1/V1I1P_20_04_03.pdf </font> </a> <br><br>\r\nI am the founder and CEO of ‘Volunteer Tech’ volunteering program and provide free of cost general computer skills and computing research methods training to the community, especially to marginalized ones  in collaboration with Virtual computer training center since May 2016. Also, I am participating in another volunteer program named ‘MENNA Elderly and Mental Illness Support Centre’ as a General Service provider such as paying 100 ETB monthly fees to support the center, washing elder and Mental Illnesses’ clothes, encouraging others to join the center and support the Centre in various activities as much as they can, provide IT related services such as maintaining office machines in the center such as computer, preparing Banners for adverting the center and many more.      \r\n<br><br>\r\nMy immediate goal is to secure a position at a Research or Software Company where I can continue to grow and improve myself both personally and professionally that leads me to be an asset for my home country and even the world by implementing my problem-solving skills and expertise into practice in the area of computing as well as to touch the lives of as many people as possible, empowering them to achieve personal and career happiness and success.\r\n<br><br>\r\nI enjoy challenges and look forward to opportunities where I will be able to assume more responsibilities. I would like to have excellent technical skills that can be achieved by securing a challenging position, demonstrating the skills as software engineer and Researcher effectively. Learning is really important to me. I want to continue learning techniques that will make me a better leader, software engineer and researcher. As I mature as a professional- I hope to take over a leadership role for the next generation of analytical researchers and Software Professionals.\r\n<br><br>\r\n Ultimately, I am a big fan of focusing on the topics of full stack software development and innovative technologies, Data analysis, leadership development, volunteering programs and have a strong passion to touch the lives of as many people as possible, empowering them to achieve personal and career happiness and success.<br><br>\r\nI developed this simple blog as my project for ALX software engineering program. <br> <br> Aklilu Mandefro, Gondar, Ethiopia\r\n', 'Gondar,Ethiopia', 'aklilu.mandefro@yahoo.com', '+251 929 24 7472', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d100949.24429313939!2d-122.44206553967531!3d37.75102885910819!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x80859a6d00690021%3A0x4a501367f076adff!2sPiassa%2C+Gondar+Ethiopia!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1');

